09/04/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Four days after the country's official acceptance as a member of the Alliance, Albania has appointed its mission to NATO headquarters in Brussels, local media reported on Wednesday (April 8th). Permanent representative for Albania Artur Kuko will lead the mission. Also on Wednesday, Tirana witnessed a ceremonial raising of the flags of all NATO member countries. (Shqip, Gazeta Shqiptare - 09/04/09; Top Channel, Top News - 08/04/09)
